<div class="main-content">
<article>

<div style="border:1px solid gray; width:90%; margin:10px auto; padding:5px 0 10px 0; border-radius: 10px; text-align:center;">
<span style="text-align:center;">Check out my latest book!</span><br />
 
<a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09KT7KX9X" target="_blank"><i>Smartphone Astrophotography <br />An Introduction to Photographing the Heavens</i></a>
</div>



<p>Learn astrophotography and take pictures of the wonders of the universe! Shoot the stars and constellations, Moon, planets, comets, nebulas, galaxies, eclipses, meteor showers and conjunctions!</p>

<p>You will find examples of all the different kinds of astrophotography here, tips for how to take astrophotos, and techniques for processing them to produce beautiful images. </p>

<ul>
    <li><a href="html/images.html">Example Images</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
    <li><a href="html/astrophotography/toc_ap.html">How-To Articles</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
	<li><a href="html/astrophotography/toc_equipment.html">Recommended Equipment</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
	<li><a href="html/processing/toc_dig.html">Processing Techniques</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
    <li><a href="html/books.html">How-To Books</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ul> 

<p>Start simple with <a href="html/beginner/crescent_moon.html">scenic shots in the twilight</a> or some <a href="html/beginner/winter_star_trails.html">star trails</a>. There are all kinds of celestial events and objects that <a href="html/astrophotography/toc_tri.html">you can shoot on a fixed tripod</a>. Sensor technology is so good today, you can even shoot astrophotos with a <a href="html/smartphone/smartphone.html">smartphone</a>.</p>

<p><a href="html/deepsky/deepsky.html">Deep-sky objects</a> in the night sky such as nebulas and galaxies are <i>very</i> faint and <i>very</i> far away. Some require <a href="html/deepsky/taurus_molecular_cloud.html">exposures that are hours long</a>. </p>

<p><a href="html/planetary/planetary.html">High-resolution planetary images</a> reveal details on amazing solar system objects like the <a href="html/planetary/saturn_20120315.html">Saturn</a>, <a href="html/planetary/jupiter_20121017.html">Jupiter</a>, <a href="html/planetary/mars_20120315.html">Mars</a>, the <a href="html/planetary/20120712_solar_prominence.html">Sun</a> and the <a href="html/planetary/copernicus_eratosthenes.html">Moon</a>.</p>

<p>Other special astronomical events like the <a href="html/eclipse/2017_total_solar_eclipse.html">2017 Total Solar Eclipse</a>, and comets <a href="html/comets/comet_hyakutake.html">Hyakutake</a>,  and <a href="html/comets/comet_neowise.html">NEOWISE</a> have made some incredible images as well as some favorite memories.</p>

<p>Also check out my <a href="html/equipment/toc_tests.html">equipment reviews</a>, and <a href="html/videos/videos.html">videos</a>.</p>

<p>I've been doing this for almost 50 years now, and even have some ancient <a href="html/film/film.html">astrophotos taken on film</a> from the last millennium, and a section on <a href="html/astrophotography/toc_film.html">film astrophotography techniques</a>.</p>

<p>If you are just starting out as a <a href="books/bgda/bgda_index.html">beginner</a>, or have fallen in love with the hobby and want to know a lot more, check out my in-depth <a href="html/books.html">digital astrophotography books</a> with detailed explanations and step-by-step instructions to help you take beautiful astronomical images. </p>

</article>
